>[Question]
>I'm having trouble reading equations/inequaltiies of this form
>
>0 < |x-3| < a = e/2
>
>Does this mean that the whole expression
>
>(0 < |x-3| < a) is = e/2 
>
>    or a =  e/2.
>
>I'm confused.
>
>[Difficulty]
>
>
>[Thoughts]
